Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 python3 (>= 3.11),
 python3-venv,
 python3-systemd
Description: cross-platform admin CLI for reading systemd journal entries
 simply-journal-admin is a command-line tool that reads recent systemd journal
 entries (Linux) through the APT-managed python3-systemd binding. The same code
 base also supports the Windows Event Log when installed from the MSI package.
 .
 The Debian package ships the prebuilt project wheel under
 /opt/simply-journal-admin/wheel and installs it into a dedicated virtual
 environment at /opt/simply-journal-admin/venv during postinst, so it never
 modifies the system Python interpreter. A thin wrapper at
 /usr/bin/simply-journal-admin invokes the venv entry point, and a systemd unit
 is registered to tail the journal under journald.
